    "comment": "Rationale: Title: \"Actinfilin Is a Cul3 Substrate Adaptor, Linking GluR6 Kainate Receptor Subunits to the Ubiquitin-Proteasome Pathway\"\n\nFig.3: \"Actinfilin mediates GluR6 degradation primarily through proteasomes.\"\n\nFig.7: \"Actinfilin and Cul3 negatively regulate surface expression of GluR6\"\n- \"We found that decreasing actinfilin levels via RNAi significantly increased surface GluR6 expression in dendritic spines, as assessed morphologically and by increased co-localization with PSD-95 (Fig. 7, A-D and H) and synaptophysin (Fig. 7H). Synaptic GluR6 more than doubled (Fig. 7H), and the size of the GluR6-containing puncta increased 1.8-fold (mean punctal area ± S.E.: control neurons, 0.12 ± 0.01 μm2; RNAi-AF expressing neurons, 0.22 ± 0.01 μm2). \". Experimental description: - \" Hippocampal neurons were cultured from E18 rats...\"\n- \"The complete rat actinfilin cDNA and truncations were subcloned into the pGADT7 prey...\"",
